WEBVTT

00:06.072 --> 00:08.039
(groans)

00:08.042 --> 00:10.175
What? You're in early.

00:10.177 --> 00:11.576
And doing paperwork,
no less.

00:11.578 --> 00:13.595
What gives?
I got a big night tonight, Jack.

00:13.597 --> 00:16.081
I got to be
signed off by EOT.

00:16.082 --> 00:18.200
(clears throat)
Bottom drawer.

00:18.202 --> 00:19.468
Excuse me?

00:19.470 --> 00:22.104
Item you left in
the car yesterday.

00:25.024 --> 00:27.275
What is this, a joke?
(man wolf-whistles)

00:27.277 --> 00:29.478
This isn't mine, Sarge.
GORMLEY: No joke.

00:29.480 --> 00:32.030
Detectives who had the car after
you found it assumed it was...

00:32.031 --> 00:33.565
Oh, I'm sure
that everybody assumed...

00:33.567 --> 00:35.200
Okay, we're all
adults here, okay?

00:35.202 --> 00:37.152
Can we just drop it,
please? Thank you.

00:37.154 --> 00:38.937
GORMLEY: Nothing to be embarrassed
about, Reagan.

00:38.939 --> 00:40.605
I'm sure you look
fetching in it.

00:40.607 --> 00:42.574
(laughter)
My 16th

00:42.576 --> 00:44.275
wedding anniversary,
Sarge, okay?

00:44.277 --> 00:45.877
The traditional gift
is silver hollowware.

00:45.879 --> 00:47.162
I didn't know what it was,

00:47.164 --> 00:48.463
so I got this.

00:48.465 --> 00:49.831
16 years, huh?

00:49.833 --> 00:51.466
Yup.
GORMLEY: With him?

00:51.468 --> 00:52.784
My condolences to Linda.

00:52.786 --> 00:54.669
You know, you take all
the potshots you want, Sarge,

00:54.671 --> 00:57.639
but 16 years ago this day,
I married the love of my life.

00:57.641 --> 01:00.308
It's always been
a lucky day for me.

01:05.348 --> 01:07.732
(soft laugh)

01:07.734 --> 01:09.300
Look at you.

01:09.302 --> 01:11.236
Is it too much
for City Hall?

01:11.238 --> 01:13.138
No, you look,
you look so...

01:13.140 --> 01:15.273
beautiful, it... it hurts.

01:16.359 --> 01:17.859
Whoa-whoa-whoa,
stop, stop.

01:17.861 --> 01:19.244
What am I thinking?
I got to...

01:19.246 --> 01:21.646
I got to record this
to show it to our future kids.

01:21.648 --> 01:22.964
(sighs)

01:25.418 --> 01:27.335
Hello, future babies.

01:27.337 --> 01:29.487
Mommy and Daddy are...

01:29.489 --> 01:31.373
eloping.
(laughs)

01:32.491 --> 01:34.876
I didn't have time
to alter the dress.

01:34.878 --> 01:37.596
No, Alyson, you look...

01:37.598 --> 01:39.314
perfect.

01:40.850 --> 01:42.134
Johnny,

01:42.136 --> 01:43.802
I can't believe
you sprung for a limo.

01:43.804 --> 01:45.987
Wait'll you see where
we're going on the honeymoon.

01:47.390 --> 01:50.508
You look beautiful.
Thank you.

01:50.510 --> 01:52.694
Now she enters the very
expensive limousine

01:52.696 --> 01:54.696
as Miss Alyson Phillips

01:54.698 --> 01:56.314
to begin the short

01:56.316 --> 01:59.517
but amazingly awesome journey
to becoming Mrs. Johnny Evans.

01:59.519 --> 02:01.870
I love you, Johnny Evans.

02:07.677 --> 02:10.846
And with that, I bid
bachelorhood a fond farewell...

02:11.747 --> 02:12.981
Get down!

02:18.137 --> 02:21.089
Alyson... Alyson!
No, no, no, don't move. You've been shot.

02:21.091 --> 02:23.541
Are you okay? Alyson!

02:23.543 --> 02:24.926
Alyson!

02:25.761 --> 02:27.879
No, no, no, no!

02:27.881 --> 02:29.030
No!

02:31.984 --> 02:33.485
You need to hear
what went out

02:33.487 --> 02:35.987
from the mayor's office
in their morning brief.

02:37.056 --> 02:39.074
Quote...

02:39.076 --> 02:41.993
"While I have every confidence
that the NYPD will succeed

02:41.995 --> 02:43.662
"in protecting
President Valverde

02:43.664 --> 02:46.865
"while he receives critical
medical treatment in our city,

02:46.867 --> 02:49.751
"I stand with our Hispanic
constituents in my outrage

02:49.753 --> 02:52.204
that this brutal dictator has
been granted permission..""

02:52.206 --> 02:54.756
Where does it say that
a white, Irish Catholic

02:54.758 --> 02:58.126
police commissioner cannot be
as outraged as Hispanics?

02:58.128 --> 03:00.078
Well, the mayor's just
covering his bases.

03:00.080 --> 03:02.297
Man could politicize
a rainy day.

03:02.299 --> 03:04.099
We need to put
something out, Frank.

03:04.101 --> 03:05.350
I've got a draft.

03:05.352 --> 03:07.185
"In a just world,

03:07.187 --> 03:09.437
"President Valverde would
receive the same treatment here

03:09.439 --> 03:12.019
that his own people get
under his criminal regime..."

03:12.044 --> 03:12.725
The guy ordered

03:12.726 --> 03:15.110
his men to open fire
on a peaceful protest

03:15.112 --> 03:17.395
and then barred
the wounded from hospitals.

03:17.397 --> 03:19.030
Including women and children.

03:19.032 --> 03:20.532
He did that?
Two days

03:20.534 --> 03:21.933
before his phony election.

03:21.935 --> 03:25.237
If it were up to me, he would
never set foot in this city.

03:25.239 --> 03:27.122
That's good stuff.

03:27.124 --> 03:29.658
I can clean it up a little...
I was venting.

03:29.660 --> 03:31.876
This office will have
no comment for the press.

03:31.878 --> 03:33.461
Sir?
Frank?

03:33.463 --> 03:34.219
We need to have...

03:34.244 --> 03:37.029
We need to get him in
and out of the hospital

03:37.134 --> 03:39.617
for an operation--
end of story.

03:39.619 --> 03:41.286
Yes, Baker?

03:41.288 --> 03:42.470
I have your chief of intel

03:42.472 --> 03:43.788
in the conference room.
It's urgent.

03:43.790 --> 03:46.641
(sighs)

03:47.960 --> 03:50.345
(door opens)
FRANK: What do you got, Chief?

03:50.347 --> 03:51.846
We've got a situation
with Valverde.

03:51.848 --> 03:53.298
Hmm.
Narcotics has had

03:53.300 --> 03:54.799
a wire up on a drug courier

03:54.801 --> 03:56.518
from his country
for about a year.

03:56.520 --> 03:59.404
Last night, he had a special
request for "fireworks"

03:59.406 --> 04:02.240
to greet President
Valverde with.

04:02.242 --> 04:04.659
There's going to be
an assassination attempt.

04:05.494 --> 04:08.330
(sighs)

04:08.332 --> 04:10.615
It's two hours out.

04:10.617 --> 04:12.867
What do you want to do, sir?

04:12.869 --> 04:15.503
Whatever it takes.

